'''Mount Flume''' is a peak in the [[White Mountains (New Hampshire)|White Mountains]] overlooking [[Franconia Notch]]. It is {{convert|4328|ft}} tall and is accessible from the north by the [[Franconia Ridge]] Trail, from the southeast by the Osseo Trail, and from the west by the Flume Slide Trail to the Franconia Ridge Trail.

From the summit there are outstanding views to the west and to the north to Franconia Ridge.  The Flume Slide Trail is a notably steep climb and is not recommended in wet weather or snow.

